HEADWORD: Shiloh
<hw>Shi"loh</hw> <pr>(sh⟦imac⟧"l⟦omac⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.
<ets>sh⟦imac⟧l⟦omac⟧h</ets>, literally, quiet, rest, fr.
<ets>sh⟦amac⟧l⟦amac⟧h</ets> to rest.]</ety> <fld>(Script.)</fld> <def>A
word used by Jacob on his deathbed, and interpreted variously, as
⟦ldquo⟧the Messiah,⟦rdquo⟧ or as the city ⟦ldquo⟧Shiloh,⟦rdquo⟧ or as
⟦ldquo⟧Rest.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
